# Skill Triggers

## Resolution order (first match wins)
1. Read each skill's SKILL.md frontmatter `triggers:` field.
2. Match the user's request or ticket context against those triggers.
3. Invoke the first matching skill.

## Skill registry
| Skill | Path | Triggers |
|-------|------|----------|
| prodops-workflow-gate | `.cursor/skills/prodops-workflow-gate/SKILL.md` | Always — master workflow for every ticket |
| ticket-intake | `.cursor/skills/ticket-intake/SKILL.md` | JIRA ticket key mentioned, new ticket event |
| knowledge-expansion | `.cursor/skills/knowledge-expansion/SKILL.md` | "search confluence", "find related", "knowledge" |
| consultation-prompts | `.cursor/skills/consultation-prompts/SKILL.md` | Subagent invocation needed |

## Default
If no specific trigger matches → use `prodops-workflow-gate` (the master workflow always applies).
